{"Title":"Creating a Voting Booth","Contents":"<p><a href=\"about.page\">About ObjectCloud</a></p><p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note</span>:&#160; <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Voting booths are experimental ObjectCloud functionality.</span></p><p>ObjectCloud gives you control over who can vote, and who can update the question. &#160;With ObjectCloud, you can enforce that someone can only vote once by requiring that they log in through OpenID.</p><h1>Creating the Voting Booth</h1><p>Navigate to the folder where you would like to place the Voting Booth.&#160; Go to \"New File,\" select \"Voting Booth,\" and enter the name of the voting booth.&#160; (For example, in the <a target=\"\" title=\"\" href=\"walkthrough.page\">Walkthrough</a>, we created \"new file.page\" in the /Users/root folder.)</p><p>Edit the voting booth by selecting the drop-down menu next to it, and then selecting the \"Edit\" option.&#160; (For example, in the <a target=\"\" title=\"\" href=\"walkthrough.page\">Walkthrough</a>, we edited \"new file.page\" in the /Users/root folder.)</p><p>You will be able to enter both a title for the voting booth, and a question.&#160; The question can use rich text, if desired.<br/></p><h2>Setting the Options</h2><p>Voting booths have two options:</p><ul><li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Users can change their votes</span>:&#160; Check this if you'd like to allow a user to change his or her vote after voting.&#160; When this is checked, the user can only vote once.&#160; It is also a good idea to not allow \"everybody\" to vote when this is enabled.<br/></li><li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Users can see results without voting</span>:&#160; Check this if you'd like to allow a user to see the current poll results before he or she has voted.</li></ul><h2>Adding and Updating Responses</h2><p>To add a response, type it in and click \"add.\"&#160; To update a response, type in the new response and click \"update.\"</p><h2>Granting People Access to Vote</h2><p>To grant other people access to vote, edit the permissions on the voting booth.&#160; (For example, in the <a target=\"\" title=\"\" href=\"walkthrough.page\">Walkthrough</a>, we edited the permissions for \"new file.page\" in the /Users/root folder.)</p><p>The following permissions can do the following:</p><ul><li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Read</span>:&#160; Everyone with Read access can see the results of voting.</li><li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Write</span>:&#160; Everyone with Write access can vote.</li><li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Administer</span>:&#160; Everyone with Administer access can update the questions and options.</li></ul>Be careful:<br/><ul><li>If you give everyone permission to read, and require that someone votes before seeing the results, then the anonymous user won't be able to see the results.</li><li>If you give everyone permission to vote, a user can \"stuff the box\" by logging out and voting repeatedly as an anonymous user.</li></ul><h1>Voting</h1><p>View the voting booth by clicking on the .vote file.  (For example, in the <a target=\"\" title=\"\" href=\"walkthrough.page\">Walkthrough</a>, we viewed \"new file.page\" in the /Users/root folder.)</p><p>To vote, select the option and click \"vote.\"</p><p>You can link to the voting booth and send the URL to people who have access.</p><p><a href=\"about.page\">About ObjectCloud</a></p>"}